<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// In some cases the shift/extend needs to be explicitly parsed together</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// with the register, rather than as a separate operand. This is needed</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// for addressing modes where the instruction as a whole dictates the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="400"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// scaling/extend, rather than specific bits in the instruction.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="401"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// By parsing them as a single operand, we avoid the need to pass an</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// extra operand in all CodeGen patterns (because all operands need to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// have an associated value), and we avoid the need to update TableGen to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// accept operands that have no associated bits in the instruction.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
